<li>Onwuachi-Willig, Angela (2005). <a href="http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=638281" class="external text" title="http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=638281" rel="nofollow">Just Another Brother on the SCT?: What Justice Clarence Thomas Teaches Us About the Influence of Racial Identity</a>. <i>Iowa Law Review, 90</i>.</li>
<li>Presser, Stephen B. (2005, Jan.-Feb.) <a href="http://www.legalaffairs.org/issues/January-February-2005/review_presser_janfeb05.msp" class="external text" title="http://www.legalaffairs.org/issues/January-February-2005/review_presser_janfeb05.msp" rel="nofollow">Touting Thomas: The Truth about America's Most Maligned Justice</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Legal_Affairs" title="Legal Affairs">Legal Affairs</a></i>.</li>
